By Jane Chijoke Public Relations Consultants Association of Nigeria, PRCAN is scheduled to hold its breakfast meeting tagged: “Nigerian Economic Outlook for 2020, the implications for the marketing communication sector,” on Monday. A renowned economist, who is a member of the recently constituted Economic Advisory Council and also the Chief Executive Officer of Financial Derivatives Limited, Mr Bismarck Rewane will be the keynote speaker. It would also have in attendance practitioners across the marketing communication industry, including PR, Advertising and experiential marketing experts. Speaking on the event, the president of PRCAN Mr Israel Jaiye Opeyemi noted that the choice of Rewane was informed by his repertoire of knowledge and experience as far as economy policy matters are concerned. He said the lecture is organised to galvanise the Industry stakeholders on the potentials and likely challenges in 2020.